Inventory Management System (C++ Qt)

Project Overview
This project is a GUI-based Inventory Management System developed in C++ using the Qt framework. The application allows users to manage products by adding, deleting, searching, and updating inventory quantities. It was created for COP 3003 – Object-Oriented Programming.

Features
- Add products with name, quantity, and price per unit
- Automatically update quantity if the product already exists
- Display inventory in a table format
- Delete products from inventory
- Search for products by name
- Remove a specific quantity from a product
- Automatically delete a product if its quantity reaches zero
- Calculate total value (quantity × price)
- Input validation with error messages

GUI Components
The program uses:
- QLabel for field descriptions
- QLineEdit for user input
- QPushButton for actions (Add, Delete, Search, Remove Quantity)
- QTableWidget to display the inventory

The interface was built using Qt Designer and follows an event-driven structure.

Object-Oriented Concepts Used

Classes and Objects
- Item (base class)
- Product (derived class)
- MainWindow (controls GUI and logic)

Encapsulation
- Data members are protected
- Access is controlled through public getter and modifier functions

Inheritance
- Product inherits from Item

Polymorphism
- Virtual function getTotalValue() is overridden in the Product class

Abstract Class
- Item is an abstract class with a pure virtual function

Composition
- MainWindow contains a vector of Item pointers representing the inventory

Templates
- A template function is used for simple calculations

Technologies Used
- C++
- Qt Framework (Qt Widgets)
- Qt Creator
- CMake
- GitHub

How to Run

On macOS:
1. Open Qt Creator
2. Open the project folder
3. Select the Qt kit for macOS
4. Click Run

On Windows:
1. Install Qt Creator
2. Open the project
3. Select a Desktop kit
4. Build and run the program

Project Structure

InventoryManagementSystem/
|
|-- main.cpp
